   <refnamediv>
       <refname>ols1 </refname>
               <refpurpose>ordinary least squares </refpurpose>
   </refnamediv>
 
        <refsynopsisdiv>
               <title>CALLING SEQUENCE</title>
               <synopsis>[rols]=ols1(y,x)</synopsis>
        </refsynopsisdiv>
 
        <refsection>
           <title>PARAMETERS</title>
           <variablelist>
           <varlistentry>
 
           <term>Input</term>
 
<listitem><para>*  <term> y </term> =    dependent variable vector (nobs x 1)</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>*  <term> x </term> =    independent variables matrix (nobs x nvar)</para></listitem>
 
 
 
<listitem><para>&#160;</para></listitem>
 
           </varlistentry>
 
          <varlistentry>
 
          <term>Output</term>
 
<listitem><para>*  <term> rols </term> =    a tlist with:</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>&#160;  - rols('meth')  = 'ols'</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>&#160;  - rols('y')     = y data vector</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>&#160;  - rols('x')     = x data matrix</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>&#160;  - rols('nobs')  = nobs</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>&#160;  - rols('nvar')  = nvars</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>&#160;  - rols('beta')  = bhat</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>&#160;  - rols('tstat') = t-stats</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>&#160;  - rols('pvalue') = pvalue of the betas</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>&#160;  - rols('resid') = residuals</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>&#160;  - rols('vcovar') = estimated variance-covariance matrix of beta</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>&#160;  - rols('sige')  = estimated variance of the residuals</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>&#160;  - rols('sigu')  = sum of squared residuals</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>&#160;  - rols('ser')  = standard error of the regression</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>&#160;  - rols('yhat')  = yhat</para></listitem>
 
 
          </varlistentry>
          </variablelist>
        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
 One of the numerous functions performing ordinary least squares: this one assumes that x et y are already a matrix and a vector and does not provide DW, R² statistics. Used in other programs.
 
        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>EXAMPLE</title>
              <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
x=grand(15,3,'nor',0,1)
y=x*ones(3,1)+grand(15,1,'nor',0,1)
r=ols1(y,x)
 
r=ols1(y,ptrend(t,nobs))
//example taken from kpss.
 
               ]]></programlisting>
        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
